# typescript.mdc

- Use strict TypeScript
- Avoid using any
- Prefer explicit types for public APIs
- Use type inference when readability remains clear
- Prefer type aliases for unions and object shapes
- Use discriminated unions when appropriate
- Prefer readonly data structures when possible
- Use descriptive variable and function names
- Prefer early returns and guard clauses
- Avoid deeply nested conditionals
- Model invalid states out of the type system when possible
- Keep types close to their domain
- Avoid unnecessary generic complexity